<NEW>

FIREHORN nodded and turned towards the building, seemingly having no
trouble walking in front of WHEELIE, in fact his leading WHEELIE
inside would seemingly leave the gate unguarded, unless one turned
around to see another figure, looking nearly identicle to FIREHORN
step out and take his place.

ASTRA walked along side WHEELIE looking down at him curiously. "I
would thing that it is your speech that is strange." She said with a
shrug, "I have never heard one speak the like." She walked also with
her axe, but she was using more like a walking stick, her position
relaxed and even curious.

She paused for a moment and then looked back, "Yours is the
strangeness of speech, since I would think it would put some things
out of reach." She smiled as she spoke.

"Don't you go aping him Astra!" FIREHORN said as he reached the door
way to the structure. "He can't help that he speaks strangely."

The door slid open to reveal a large chamber inside. At the inside of
the door there were two other figures that looked like FIREHORN and
ASTRA, atleast in basic construction and form. They both also had
large axes that were held straight up in cerimonial fashion, both
hands grasping them firmly.

They nodded as FIREHORN and ASTRA, who nodded back, their movements
strangly regal and dignified.

"Unus is in here." ASTRA said to WHEELIE as she gestured for him to
come inside with them, no longer attempting to use his ryming speech.

(TAG)

Preston
